Package: baseballr
Title: Functions for Acquiring and Analyzing Baseball Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Bill", "Petti", email = "billpetti@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Saiem", "Gilani", email = "saiem.gilani@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ben", "Baumer", email = "ben.baumer@gmail.com", role = "ctb"),
    person("Ben", "Dilday", email = "ben.dilday.phd@gmail.com", role = "ctb"),
    person("Robert", "Frey", email = "rfrey22@gmail.com", role = "ctb"))
Description: Provides numerous functions for acquiring and analyzing baseball
    data. Data can be acquired from various online sources from within R.
    Custom metrics can also be calculated, such as wOBA, FIP, and Edge%.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6.0)
